    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Professionals that research, select, adapt, or develop texts, scripts, plays, operas, or films for a theater or other production company. Responsibilities of this position may include liason with authors, preparation of printed matter, or public relations. The role of dramaturge was originally identified in a series of essays by Gotthold Ephraim Lessing, published 1767-1769.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
